<!DOCTYPE book PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.5//EN" 
    "http://www.oasis-open.org/docbook/xml/4.5/docbookx.dtd">
<book id="devenv">
    <bookinfo>
        <title>Development Environment Overview</title>
        <issuenum>${content.version}</issuenum>
        <pubdate>${docbook.pubdate}</pubdate>
        <copyright>
            <year>${copyright.year}</year>
            <holder>${copyright.holder}</holder>
        </copyright>
        <abstract>
            <para>This presentation provides an introduction to development tools and techniques 
                for building enterprise Java applications.
            </para>
        </abstract>
    </bookinfo>
    <preface id="devenv-purpose">
        <title>Purpose</title>

        <section id="devenv-goals">
            <title>Goals</title>
            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                <listitem><para>Become familiar with the development environment 
                    used with class and commonly used for enterprise Java 
                    developments</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>

        <section id="devenv-objectives">
            <title>Objectives</title>
            <para>At the completion of this topic, the student shall</para>
            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                <listitem><para>have more understanding of:</para>
                    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                        <listitem><para>Maven project structure</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Maven project pom.xml</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Maven/Eclipse integration</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Eclipse development tasks</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
                <listitem><para>be able to:</para>
                    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                        <listitem><para>Establish a Maven project structure</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Create and execute a test for Java class</para>
                            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                                <listitem><para>within Eclipse</para></listitem>
                                <listitem><para>from Eclipse, within Maven</para></listitem>
                            </itemizedlist>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Debug a Java test and its associated class</para>
                            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                                <listitem><para>within Eclipse</para></listitem>
                                <listitem><para>from Eclipse, within Maven (remote debugging)</para></listitem>
                            </itemizedlist>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
    </preface>

